did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.unittitle: W. L. Stangel Papers, 1888-1975 and undated
did.abstract: Papers and records of W. L. Stangel, an original faculty member of Texas Technological College in 1925.

repository.label: Repository:
repository.corpname: Southwest Collection/Special Collections Library, Texas Tech University

bioghist.head: Biographical Sketch
bioghist.p: Born August 16, 1889 at Stangelville, Wisconsin, Wenzel Louis Stangel received degrees from Texas A&M and the University of Missouri. In 1920, he married Mary Ruth Canon. Stangel was one of the original Texas Technological College faculty member in 1925 and went on to establish the Animal Husbandry Department. He became Dean of College of Agriculture, chaired the Texas Technological College Athletic Council for 25 years, and published numerous works on animal science. One of the residence dormitories on the Tech campus was named after him. Stangel died 1978 in Lubbock, Texas.
The Handbook of Texas has published a more in-depth on-line biography of Wenzel Louis Stangel at http://www.tsha.utexas.edu/handbook/online/search.html

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection includes correspondence, photographs, legal and financial documents, speech notes, calendars and diaries, as well as publications and office files relating to livestock, higher education and agriculture.

arrangement.head: Organization
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged in four series: Agriculture, Education, Livestock and Personal.
